Yeah. Or, we could change the join so that the report has an empty value when there isn't a ProductionItem link? That way they know what they are...

Seems like for the 7 items that are missing, they don't have any Production Item link, and all other items do. I THINK to fix that one I need to get BLN to send me the Production Item Links (4 mil numbers) for those items.
Eric what do you think of this? Stephen? I don't have context on the purpose of these reports so I'm lost at this point

TLDR


 

  Two fixes needed:


 

  1. View Fix: Add WHERE SM.DefaultSite IS NULL OR SM.DefaultSite <> 'NRS' to the Map CTE in [Plan].[vwWeeklySiteDistribution] — this makes the view match the stored procedure fix and stops ~77% of units from being "lost" when NRS rows are filtered out.

  2. Data Fix: Insert 7 missing items into Product.ProductionItems table — these items have forecast data but can't appear in S&P Export without ProductionItems mappings. Need Bell to confirm the ProductionItemNum values.


 

  Once both are done, S&P and PFAC exports should align.

Here's Claudes answer:   

 

Issue Summary

  Comparing Mums exports:
  - S&P Export: 1,442,676 units (28 items)
  - PFAC Export (excluding NRS): 1,487,467 units (35 items)
  - Net Difference: +44,791 units

  This difference comes from two offsetting issues:
  - +128,970 units: 7 items in PFAC not appearing in S&P
  - -84,179 units: 28 shared items showing 3-9% lower in PFAC

  ---
  Fix #1: View Missing NRS Exclusion

  Problem

  The [Plan].[vwWeeklySiteDistribution] view includes NRS stores in its distribution percentage calculation. When NRS rows are filtered out after export, those units disappear rather than being redistributed.

  - NRS stores represent 77.5% of SiteMaps mappings (9,288 of 11,983)
  - The stored procedure fix excludes NRS before calculating percentages
  - The view still includes NRS, causing ~5-9% lower unit counts for non-NRS stores

  Fix Required

  Update the View's Map CTE to exclude NRS before distribution calculation.

  File: [Plan].[vwWeeklySiteDistribution]

  Current Code (around line 3-13):
  , Map AS
  (
      SELECT DISTINCT
          LocationID = L.ID
          , RegionID = L.RegionID
          , ProgramID = SM.ProgramID
          , [Site] = SM.DefaultSite
      FROM Customer.Locations L
      INNER JOIN Customer.SiteMaps SM
          ON SM.LocationID = L.ID
  )

  Updated Code:
  , Map AS
  (
      SELECT DISTINCT
          LocationID = L.ID
          , RegionID = L.RegionID
          , ProgramID = SM.ProgramID
          , [Site] = SM.DefaultSite
      FROM Customer.Locations L
      INNER JOIN Customer.SiteMaps SM
          ON SM.LocationID = L.ID
      WHERE
          SM.DefaultSite IS NULL
          OR SM.DefaultSite <> 'NRS'
  )

  This matches the fix already applied to [Plan].[DistributeRegionForecast].

  ---
  Fix #2: Missing ProductionItems Mappings

  Problem

  The S&P Export ([Plan].[ExportSalesAndProductionItems]) uses an INNER JOIN to Product.ProductionItems to get production attributes (Genus, Series, Color, Category, MixPct). Items without a ProductionItems record are excluded from the export.

  7 Mum items exist in Product.Items and have forecast data, but have no record in Product.ProductionItems:

  | ItemID | ItemNumber | Description                  | Forecast Units |
  |--------|------------|------------------------------|----------------|
  | 153409 | 1003977    | MUM WINCHESTER POT YELLOW #8 | 29,934         |
  | 153177 | 1003980    | MUM WINCHESTER POT ORANGE #8 | 23,420         |
  | 153183 | 1004000    | MUM TRICOLOR 3 GAL           | 23,131         |
  | 153410 | 1003978    | MUM WINCHESTER POT PURPLE #8 | 19,553         |
  | 153299 | 1003979    | MUM WINCHESTER POT RED #8    | 16,820         |
  | 153408 | 1003976    | MUM WINCHESTER POT WHITE #8  | 8,462          |
  | 150065 | 1000638    | FLAIR MUM PLANTER #13 BN     | 7,650          |

  Fix Required

  Insert records into Product.ProductionItems for each missing item.

  Table: Product.ProductionItems

  Required Columns:
  | Column            | Type          | Required | Notes                             |
  |-------------------|---------------|----------|-----------------------------------|
  | ProductionItemNum | nvarchar(128) | Yes      | Bell's production item number     |
  | Genus             | nvarchar(200) | Yes      | Use CHRYSANTHEMUM for Mums        |
  | Series            | nvarchar(200) | Yes      | Production series identifier      |
  | Color             | nvarchar(200) | Yes      | Use * for mixed or specific color |
  | Category          | nvarchar(200) | Yes      | See suggested values below        |
  | MixPct            | decimal       | No       | Default 100 if null               |
  | StartWeek         | int           | No       | Optional week range filter        |
  | EndWeek           | int           | No       | Optional week range filter        |
  | ItemID            | int           | Yes      | FK to Product.Items.ID            |

  Suggested Categories (based on existing patterns):
  - Winchester Pot #8 items → 08INMUM
  - Tricolor 3 GAL → 3GALMUM or similar
  - Flair Planter #13 → 13INMUM

  Example INSERT (template - values need confirmation from Bell):
  INSERT INTO Product.ProductionItems
      (ProductionItemNum, Genus, Series, Color, Category, MixPct, ItemID)
  VALUES
      -- MUM WINCHESTER POT YELLOW #8
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'WINCHESTER', 'YELLOW', '08INMUM', 100, 153409),

      -- MUM WINCHESTER POT ORANGE #8
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'WINCHESTER', 'ORANGE', '08INMUM', 100, 153177),

      -- MUM TRICOLOR 3 GAL
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'TRICOLOR', '*', '3GALMUM', 100, 153183),

      -- MUM WINCHESTER POT PURPLE #8
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'WINCHESTER', 'PURPLE', '08INMUM', 100, 153410),

      -- MUM WINCHESTER POT RED #8
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'WINCHESTER', 'RED', '08INMUM', 100, 153299),

      -- MUM WINCHESTER POT WHITE #8
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'WINCHESTER', 'WHITE', '08INMUM', 100, 153408),

      -- FLAIR MUM PLANTER #13 BN
      ('TBD', 'CHRYSANTHEMUM', 'FLAIR', '*', '13INMUM', 100, 150065);

  Note: The ProductionItemNum values need to be provided by Bell - these are their internal production item numbers that map to their Produce system.

Okay was using Claude to help me drill down as well, and this is what we got:

 

Summary


 

  After comparing the S&P Export and PFAC Export for Mums, I've identified the root causes of the discrepancies between the two reports.


 

  ---

  Key Findings


 

  1. Both exports now use the same distribution logic

  - [Plan].[DistributeRegionForecast] stored procedure - updated by Eric on 2026-01-09

  - [Plan].[vwWeeklySiteDistribution] view - also updated 2026-01-09

  - Both now exclude NRS (Not Regularly Serviced) stores and normalize distribution percentages


 

  2. The ~45K unit difference is NOT due to rounding


 

  The math breaks down as follows:


 

  | Source                      | Units     |

  |-----------------------------|-----------|

  | S&P Export Total            | 1,442,676 |

  | PFAC Export (excluding NRS) | 1,487,467 |

  | Net Difference              | +44,791   |


 

  This difference comes from two offsetting factors:

  - +128,970 units: 7 items appear in PFAC but NOT in S&P

  - -84,179 units: 28 shared items show 3-9% fewer units in PFAC than S&P


 

  3. Root Cause: 7 Items Missing from Product.ProductionItems


 

  The S&P Export ([Plan].[ExportSalesAndProductionItems]) joins to Product.ProductionItems. Items without a mapping in that table are excluded from the export.


 

  These 7 items exist in Product.Items but have NO entry in Product.ProductionItems:


 

  | ItemNumber | Description                  | PFAC Units | ItemID |

  |------------|------------------------------|------------|--------|

  | 1003977    | MUM WINCHESTER POT YELLOW #8 | 29,934     | 153409 |

  | 1003980    | MUM WINCHESTER POT ORANGE #8 | 23,420     | 153177 |

  | 1004000    | MUM TRICOLOR 3 GAL           | 23,131     | 153183 |

  | 1003978    | MUM WINCHESTER POT PURPLE #8 | 19,553     | 153410 |

  | 1003979    | MUM WINCHESTER POT RED #8    | 16,820     | 153299 |

  | 1003976    | MUM WINCHESTER POT WHITE #8  | 8,462      | 153408 |

  | 1000638    | FLAIR MUM PLANTER #13 BN     | 7,650      | 150065 |

  | TOTAL      |                              | 128,970    |        |


 

  4. PFAC Export Still Shows NRS Rows


 

  The PFAC file I analyzed still contained 3,990 NRS rows (92,708 units). If this export comes from the View directly rather than the stored procedure, it may need verification that the correct source is being used.
